on saturday 19th of november saturday we have the international mens day being celebrated around the world and i think we can also observe the occasion amongst ourselves we know that throughout history women and non binary people have suffered a lot but we shouldnt forget that men have been subject to many hardships because of their gender as well i wrote to satrangi about the same but have not received a reply and satrangi probably doesnt celebrate such events either from what little i know about the club so its up to us if you guys feel that we should do something lets make a plan and do it if enough people are interested we can all meet the next weekend and brainstorm some ideas and make the plan for the 19th we can have a private celebration amongst 510 close friends where we can watch a documentary or a movie go out and do something manly share our experiences and talk about the things that we have to deal with because of our gender or anything that we want we can talk about how indian men our fathers work hard to provide for us and probably dont ever get their fair share of credit we can talk about how some of us feel having grown up with little to no validation because we dont really get compliments if we are not in a relationship we can talk about how if women were having problems getting voting rights in the twentieth century then men were having problems getting killed like animals in the two world wars and all the other conflicts that happened then i saw saving private ryan and the movie 1917 through this lens and it was really disturbing to see all the men in it suffer so much not wanting to be there but forcibly conscripted because of the gender i imagine them thinking if it would have been better if they were born a girl and they could have saved themselves this traumatizing ordeal there are many things to talk about and this could be an opportunity for catharsis for people who might want to share related stories

daylight savings exactly hota kya h
same question
its a way to basically fudge your clock time so that you get max sun time
since us is even more to the north than us they end up getting less sun time when following the conventional clock times so they basically add time to redefine the standard clock time like theyll usually add one hour so that the sunset happens earlier
sunrise happens at say 5 am instead of the usual 6 am so they subtract an hour call 5 to be 6 so that more of the daytime has the sun out

httpsfeminisminindiacom20230116whyarethereonlyafewwomeniniitsandiisers
according to priyanka bsms iiser pune 2022 approaching professors for admission into their labs is a more daunting task for women and nonbinary students than for men since most professors are also men male professors usually remain more informal with male students right from the beginning which facilitates the initial conversation of working together but the exclusion from this informal circle also makes it challenging for other students to reach out to professors
in several iit and iiser campuses there are no informal physical spaces for women and men to interact regularly for example iit jodhpur and iiser pune do not allow movement into another genders residence halls at all

guys i want to send this mail to girish asap
let me know if anyone wants to cosign it
its not allowed anymore
last year senate meeting voted against it
many reasons some being difficulties in grading
allowing external advisors to grade you for a semester project is not allowed
it wasnt legally allowed for years though
there were some sneaky ways which are now disallowed as well
this makes fair sense to me
yeah it was never allowed people who wanted to do a project under an external prof contacted an iiser prof to sign off and pretend to be your supervisor on paper
despite being against institute rules girish was cool with people exploiting this loophole
recently  the senate became aware that an increasingly large number of students are scamming their way through they thus issued another guideline asking profs to refrain from helping students credit external sem projects
if you really wanna do an external project  there are only two ways 1find a cosupervisor within iiser so that it becomes a collaborative project one that where you are primarily under an internal prof but also in contact with external dude for guidance
2 find a professor whos nice enough to sign off despite the senate ruling
i was in the same boat last year i first attempted 1 but to no avail however after several requests a prof who knew me well agreed to sign off for the project
